# scrontab entries for the JWST-GC MAST monitor (HiPerGator).
#
# Activation: on a HiPerGator login node run `scrontab -e` and paste these entries
# (or `scrontab < docs/scrontab.example` to REPLACE your scrontab -- careful if you
# already have entries).  scrontab runs each entry as a SLURM job; the #SCRON lines
# above an entry are its sbatch directives.  Check with `scrontab -l`;
# jobs appear in `squeue --me` at the scheduled times.
#
# Both entries are metadata-only (anonymous MAST queries + a JSON state file):
# tiny resource ask.  Log directory must exist:
#   mkdir -p /blue/adamginsburg/adamginsburg/logs/jwst

# ---- daily: AUTO mode (decision 2026-07-22: download + trigger + report +
#      commit-state, all --execute).  Gates: free disk space (--min-free-tb,
#      checked against the --download-dir filesystem), the first-run SEED guard
#      (a missing/empty state file commits a baseline instead of submitting the
#      whole backlog -- or run `... mast_monitor --seed` once at deployment),
#      and the --max-submit cap (default 4 (program,obs) groups per run; more
#      downgrades the run to report-only).  Any failed gate posts a loud
#      warning on the QA issue instead of downloading/submitting.
#
#      --time=00:30:00: every MAST request is now individually time-bounded
#      (astroquery.mast.conf.timeout = 120 s, set by the code), so a hung
#      request can no longer eat the whole allocation -- 30 min is ample for
#      the metadata poll + a handful of submissions.  If you EXPECT --auto to
#      be actively downloading new releases (large uncal/i2d batches), raise
#      to --time=04:00:00 so the transfer itself has room.
#SCRON --account=astronomy-dept
#SCRON --qos=astronomy-dept-b
#SCRON --job-name=jwstgc-mastmon-daily
#SCRON --cpus-per-task=1
#SCRON --mem=4gb
#SCRON --time=00:30:00
#SCRON --output=/blue/adamginsburg/adamginsburg/logs/jwst/mast_monitor_%j.log
17 7 * * * cd /blue/adamginsburg/adamginsburg/repos/data-qa && /blue/adamginsburg/adamginsburg/miniconda3/envs/python313/bin/python -m data_qa.mast_monitor --auto --min-free-tb 5 --download-dir /orange/adamginsburg/jwst/ops/downloads

# ---- report-only alternative (the pre-AUTO daily entry): poll + print, touch
#      nothing.  TO SWAP: comment out the AUTO entry above and delete ONE
#      leading '#' from every line below (##SCRON -> #SCRON, '#17 7' -> '17 7').
##SCRON --account=astronomy-dept
##SCRON --qos=astronomy-dept-b
##SCRON --job-name=jwstgc-mastmon-daily
##SCRON --cpus-per-task=1
##SCRON --mem=4gb
##SCRON --time=00:30:00
##SCRON --output=/blue/adamginsburg/adamginsburg/logs/jwst/mast_monitor_%j.log
#17 7 * * * cd /blue/adamginsburg/adamginsburg/repos/data-qa && /blue/adamginsburg/adamginsburg/miniconda3/envs/python313/bin/python -m data_qa.mast_monitor

# ---- weekly (Mondays): poll + COMMIT the state, so a report-only daily would
#      only re-report events younger than a week.  Redundant while the daily
#      --auto entry commits state itself, but harmless (and it keeps the state
#      fresh if the daily entry is ever swapped back to report-only).
#SCRON --account=astronomy-dept
#SCRON --qos=astronomy-dept-b
#SCRON --job-name=jwstgc-mastmon-weekly
#SCRON --cpus-per-task=1
#SCRON --mem=4gb
#SCRON --time=00:30:00
#SCRON --output=/blue/adamginsburg/adamginsburg/logs/jwst/mast_monitor_commit_%j.log
47 7 * * 1 cd /blue/adamginsburg/adamginsburg/repos/data-qa && /blue/adamginsburg/adamginsburg/miniconda3/envs/python313/bin/python -m data_qa.mast_monitor --commit-state
